<title>USA: Sierra evaluating Physician.</title>
<headline>Sierra evaluating Physician.</headline>
<dateline>LAS VEGAS 1997-03-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Sierra Health Services Inc said Thursday it will continue to evaluate the viability of a potential merger with Physician Corp of America.</p>
<p>Sierra said it has been re-evaluating the proposed deal since February 20, when Physician Corp said it would take significant additional charges in the fourth quarter of 1996.</p>
<p>&quot;We hope to find an alternative, but only if it is in the best interest of our shareholders,&quot; said Sierra Chairman and Chief Executive Officer Anthony Marlon.</p>
<p>Marlon said if Sierra decided to pursue a deal it would renegotiate the terms and announce them by March 31.</p>
